    <Note Title="Topic" Type="Summary" Ordinal="1" xml:lang="en">Security update for lxc</Note>
    <Note Title="Details" Type="General" Ordinal="2" xml:lang="en">lxc was updated to fix two security issues.

The following vulnerabilities were fixed:

* CVE-2015-1331: directory traversal flaw allowing arbitrary file creation as the root user (bnc#938522)
* CVE-2015-1334: AppArmor or SELinux confinement escape via fake /proc (bnc#938523)
</Note>
